; TUPLECMP simplification over @unique foreign constants: the RED fact can
; never satisfy C = BLUE (distinct unique constants are provably unequal, the
; body is deleted and the compare replaced by its false_body), while
; message-fed rows must still be compared at runtime.

#foreign Tok ```int```.
#constant Tok RED ```1``` @unique.
#constant Tok BLUE ```2``` @unique.

#message like(Tok C).
#local likes(Tok C).
likes(RED).
likes(C) : like(C).

#query result(free Tok C).
result(C) : likes(C), C = BLUE.

#query all_likes(free Tok C).
all_likes(C) : likes(C).
